, from dance music to gay pornography, from "tube" maps to the role of Bangladeshi communities in shaping contemporary London politics. Broadly interdisciplinary and deeply attentive to London's historical diversity, the book is unified by its attention to a single question: How have the many imaginations and representations of London shaped—and been shaped by—history and culture? The answers provided within this volume offer the chance to view London in surprising new ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aArea Studies : British Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh1 aEade, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFremeaux, Isabelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarbin, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilbert, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilbert, Pamela K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilbert, Pamela K., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHenderson, Fiona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolder, Heidi J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaplan, Morris B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLevenson, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMonroe, Alexei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPike, David L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPremnath, Gautam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSipe, Michelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWolfreys, Julian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabular